James is seeking edits to his cover letter for an Assistant Professor position in the Climate Systems Engineering initiative at the University of Chicago. Arachne suggests rephrasing to highlight James' unique perspective, experience, and enthusiasm in the intersection of economic and environmental systems. She advises emphasizing the integrative role of his research on climate change risks and modeling in supporting the CSEi's vision. Arachne also suggests mentioning James' involvement in bridging academia and policy-making, including workshops and advisory roles for governmental and intergovernmental bodies. Finally, she recommends mentioning James' experience in educational outreach and the development of multidisciplinary courses.
